Before using Smart Assistant, please read carefully and agree to the following terms. \101. Smart Assistant provides a content generation service under the voice assistant, as well as a smart summary generation service under the meeting assistant and Translator. Smart Assistant is built based on the generative AI technology. It is designed with safety as a priority, but it may still provide biased, incorrect, harmful, or misleading responses. Therefore, do not rely on its advice. \102. Smart Assistant uses your input as a prompt to output the corresponding text content under the voice assistant. Based on the text transcribed from your voice in the meeting assistant and Translator as input, it generates a smart summary generation service. \103. The content you enter and that Smart Assistant generates for you will be retained until you delete them. \104. Do not share sensitive or confidential information. If you do this, Smart Assistant will use such information. \105. We share information with our service providers. \10For more information (including how to delete your information), see the \"Privacy Policy\". If you do not agree with these terms, you will be unable to use the generative AI services in the voice assistant, meeting assistant, and Translator. However, this will not affect your ability to use other features that do not involve generative AI.

Before using the voice assistant, you need to read and agree to the rules in our 《Privacy Policy》 for processing personal information related to the voice assistant carefully. When you use this function, we will collect and use your recording data, voice transcription information, custom device identifier, contact information, address information, SIM card phone number (Android 14 and above only), city and location information, and Flyme account information. This information allows us to provide voice interaction services, including making or hanging up phone calls through the voice assistant and displaying navigation information and local weather information on your glasses based on voice commands. When you use the voice assistant, your conversation records will be bound to the Flyme account you have logged in with to synchronize your conversation records and provide a more consistent experience. For more details, please refer to the relevant sections of the 《Privacy Policy》. You can also use generative AI services from third-party large language model service providers through the voice assistant. We will share the text information generated from your input text or voice transcription with third-party service providers. Before using these third-party services, please ensure you have read and agreed to the third party\'s user agreement and privacy policy.

To use the navigation, you need to read and agree to the rules in our 《Privacy Policy》 for processing personal information related to the navigation carefully. When you use this function, we will collect and use your voluntarily provided common address information, location information, navigation route planning, departure and destination, city, province, country region, and coordinate system information to provide positioning and navigation functions. For more details, please refer to the relevant sections of the 《Privacy Policy》.

To ensure you can use our products and services, please read and agree to our MYVU App\'s 《Privacy Policy》 and 《Service Agreement》. The above agreement will help you understand how we collect, use, store, and share your personal information and your related rights. Regarding the important content of the above Privacy Policy, we would like to inform you of the following:\10\10 (1) The basic functions of MYVU are designed to be to used with smart wearable devices, such as glasses, so it is necessary to apply for location permission, Bluetooth permission, and notification permission to discover devices and maintain the connection status between devices. Certain models of smart glasses will require an IMU (Inertial Measurement Unit) to enable Pinned-in-space mode;\10\10 (2) MYVU and the matching Glasses provide a variety of functions such as voice assistant, which you can choose to enable or disable. We will inform you of the purpose for applying for the permissions involved in the functions. You can also disable the permissions in the MYVU app\'s permission management at any time;\10\10 (3) Regarding the information we collecte and share, you can check the 《Personal Information Collection Checklist》 and 《Third Party Information Sharing Checklist》 at any time in the MYVU App; (4) We will use industry-leading security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access;\10\10 (5) You can view, modify, and delete personal information, withdraw consent, and cancel your account in the MYVU App. (6) This product/service may pair with, connect to and manage multiple glasses, for which there is a strategy for connection priorities in place. Data processing activities may vary among devices.
